doc.after: The Australian Recording Industry Association ARIA is a trade group representing the Australian recording industry which was established in 1983 by six major record companies EMI Festival CBS RCA WEA and Universal replacing the Association of Australian Record Manufacturers AARM which was formed in 1956 1 It oversees the collection administration and distribution of music licenses and royalties
